LIBRADIO INSTALL file
$Id$
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Basic Installation
==================
These are generic installation instructions.

The simplest way to compile this package is:

  1. 'cd' to the directory containing the package's source code.

  2. Type 'make' to compile the package.

  3. Type 'sudo make install' to install the programs.

  4. You can remove the program binaries and object files from the
     source code directory by typing 'make clean'.

  5. Type 'sudo make uninstall' if you wish uninstall the programs.

When the installation is done, you can then compile the demo programs found in
the examples directory (cd examples/aprs && make && ./demo_aprs).

For radio Python module, It is necessary to install swig and 
python-serial, for example on a debian system, you need to :

  1. Type 'sudo apt-get install swig python-serial'

  2. 'cd' to the directory python of this package

  3. Type 'python setup.py build_ext' to compile the package.

  4. Type 'sudo python setup.py install' to install the programs.

  5. Type 'sudo ldconfig' to udpate symbolic links for the shared libraries

When the installation is done, you can then execute the demo programs found in
the examples directory (cd python/examples/aprs && python demo_aprs.py).

Installation Names
==================

By default, 'make install' will install the package's files in
'/usr/local/bin', '/usr/local/man', etc.  You can specify an
installation prefix other than '/usr/local' by giving 'make' the
option 'prefix=PATH' after target install/uninstall.
